  "analysis": "The task requires implementing a temperature controller with specific performance metrics. The system involves calibration, parameter estimation, controller tuning, and closed-loop control. The available skills include first-order-model-fitting, imc-tuning-rules, and scipy-curve-fit, which are relevant for parameter estimation and controller design. The current terminal state is empty, indicating no prior commands have been executed.",
  "plan": [
    "Load the first-order-model-fitting skill to assist with parameter estimation",
    "Run a calibration test to collect temperature data over 30 seconds with 20+ data points",
    "Estimate system parameters (K and tau) from the calibration data using the first-order-model-fitting skill",
    "Calculate PI controller gains using the estimated parameters and IMC tuning rules",
    "Implement closed-loop control to maintain the temperature at 22.0C",
    "Log the control data and calculate performance metrics"
  ],
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 hvac_simulator.py --calibration --duration 30 --output calibration_log.json\n",
      "duration": 1.0
